annotation.TEXT: I'm guessing it dings twice because I'm super, and there are two custom blocks that ding when I pass through them. However, it seems that I'm not hitting them both at the exact same time, so two dings are audible.
Well, this door's different from the last one, but is it any good?
Hey, I can go down this pipe, and it leads... to the exit?! Wow, that's surprising, but I'm not complaining!
Okay, this time, I'll skip this door. Also, I'm not going to bother with the "III" coin below, although it should be obvious how to get it.
Power ups seem to be scarce in this level...
Alright, this level's done, but I'm curious as to what's beyond the pipe I went down...
Let's rewind and find out!
Alright, we're heading into "Trilogy Castle" this time. Let's check it out!
Argh! The super-ultra-mega-large fire-bar got me! (Also, that thing's moving fast!)
Of course, that jump is tricky unless I'm in the SMB2 zone.
Ah, so this is like those maze sections of SMB1... sort of.
Nope, but I'm betting there's something good in those fire-bar guarded bricks...
Uh, oh. Beezo and Snifit are joining forces, but I can get past them! (I'm wondering if any Shyguys or Bob-ombs will start coming out of these jars at some point...)

Well, I think I'm done with this level. It was a pretty cool level, although it could use more power ups and some other touch ups. Next time, I start taking on the east side of the map! To be continued...
And right there, I guess I rubbed up against multiple "wrong" SFX blocks before hitting a warp block. Hey, could I maybe "detect" the wrong path, then turn around before hitting the warp?
Okay, let's explore this SMB2 area for now.
Door number 2's a bust...
Another Panser, and a key, and... Oh, no! Not him! Anything but him!!!

Okay, so I screen transitioned...
Okay, koopa. You're coming with me!

Can't go forward any more, so it's time to go in the door!
Uh, oh. A Maverick Thwomp. Should be easy enough to get past.
I should be able to get in that door without too much difficulty...
Of course, the trick will be hitting them...

Let's explore the other parts of this level that I didn't fully check out yet.

Totally awesome!

Yet another "III" coin...
Run, run! Or you'll be well done!
Argh! Why does Panser jump here?! I don't remember any Pansers being able to jump in SMB2!
Also, we got Roto-discs (AKA Nuclear Waffles).
Hmm... Should I go in that door?
What? A dead end? Wait, do I have to enter one of the jars?
Oh, cool! We've got some SMB1-style graphics here!
Whoa, I almost missed my ride there!
There sure are a lot of jars around here...
I kind of want that mushroom...
Oh, it looks like there's a flaw in the level design there anyway, so good thing for that shortcut!
Moving on... (By the way, I didn't rewind at all in this part. I just decided to cut out the repeated travelling through familiar ground in an effort to shorten the video a little bit.)
Hmm... A pipe, and what appears to be an enterable door...
Okay, I got to the key with an extra hit this time, so I should be able to make it back down.
Sure, why not?
I don't consider that a fair death, so I used a rewind. Let's just label that one "science" and move on.
Whew! Found the right jar before I got clobbered!
Yes, I'm going to check every brick here too. You never know where a multi-coin block might be hidden...

Oh, god. Panser! Wait... Since when could Pansers jump? This looks tricky!
I think I can take a shortcut here! Sorry, Shyguys!
Dang it! Well, there's only enough time to try one more door, but which one?
At least I can get a reserve mushroom.
Well, by skipping that door, I wind up in this familiar place, so let's rewind a bit and actually enter that door.
Okay, remember this room, where I rode a Beezo over the spikes to the right? Well, let's go left this time!
A "III" coin that probably wasn't worth going for.
Oh, crap! Where did that second Phanto come from?

Is it safe to assume that these conveyor belts aren't acting quite correctly?
And... that's it for this path, but I wonder where else I haven't explored yet...
Nope. Apparently, there are one-way blocks here too, so I'm forced to hit the warp.
Yawn...
Okay, what about the SMB1 zone here?
More breakable bricks, but I'm thinking they won't contain any items at all, so I'm not going to waste time breaking them all any more.

A vertical area, with a floating door. I wonder if I'll need a mushroom block (or maybe just another key)...
Oh, I went straight from SMB3 to SMB2 this time. Also, I think I know how to cross that pit now!
...Nor that pipe, and then I hit a warp taking me back. So, I had to take that first pipe to finish the level.

Nothing of interest over here...

The third door fails.

No, not the cheepos!

Well, there's a "III" coin, which I guess I can collect, since I brought a shell with me.

I can't go right from here, so I guess I'll go back and ride the Beezo in the SMB2 part again.

Good thing I did stick around, so that I could unlock this door! (Also, I got another "III" coin. Hmm...)

Hmm... Maybe I can scroll Panser's fireballs off screen like I did with the Hammer Brother's hammers in that other level...
